[1] Beaver, human exposure - New York/Pennsylvania
Date: Mon 13 Aug 2012
Source: The Salt Lake Tribune, Associated Press (AP) report [edited]
http://www.sltrib.com/sltrib/world/54688633-68/beaver-rabid-swimming-scout.html.csp


A Boy Scout leader from New York who was attacked by a rabid beaver while swimming in the Delaware River is recovering.

The Poughkeepsie Journal reports that the 51 year old victim, of Pine Plains (NY), was swimming in eastern Pennsylvania on 2 Aug 2012 when a beaver swam through his legs and bit him in the chest.

The animal then bit him in the leg, buttocks, arm, hand, and torso before he managed to grab it and hold its jaw closed.

One Boy Scout pulled the victim to shore, where he tossed the beaver away from him. The Scouts then used rocks to kill the animal.

A doctor confirmed the beaver had rabies a day after the attack. Dutchess County health officials say a rabid beaver attack is unusual.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail rapporteur Mary Marshall

[This appears to be an update of the cases previously reported as Rabies - USA (17): (PA), beaver 20120805.1228835.

It would be an excellent time to remind people to update the rabies vaccination of their pets, including any large animals, such as horses or other livestock show animals, especially those being handled on a regular to daily basis. - Mod.TG

